DATA CLOUD
Configurations

Use these configuration steps to welcome new loyalty members to your program.

Connect Loyalty Management to Marketing Cloud Engagement

Implement Marketing Cloud Connect to connect Marketing Cloud Engagement and Loyalty Management.

Configure Marketing Cloud Engagement and Marketing Cloud Connect.
In Salesforce, assign the Loyalty Management permission set to the Marketing Cloud Connect system user.
In Salesforce, for the Marketing Cloud Engagement system user profile, select Marketing User.
To ensure proper mapping, synchronize the Loyalty data extensions in this order.
Contact and User
Loyalty Program and Campaign
Loyalty Tier Group and Campaign Member
Loyalty Program Currency, Loyalty Program Member, Loyalty Tier, Loyalty Tier Benefit, and Voucher Definition
Loyalty Member Currency, Loyalty Member Tier, Promotion, and Transaction Journal
Loyalty Ledger and Voucher
Install the Loyalty Management Content Blocks managed package for Marketing Cloud Engagement.
Welcome New Loyalty Members to Your Program via Marketing Cloud Engagement
Build an email in Marketing Cloud Engagement welcoming members to your loyalty program.
Create a Welcome Journey in Marketing Cloud Engagement to deliver personalized loyalty welcome emails to members.
Add wait periods, splits, and defined customer touchpoints.
To capture newly enrolled loyalty members, define a Salesforce data entry based on the Loyalty Program Member object.

Some marketing campaigns related to your Loyalty Program require using queries for journey entry. Use the query’s resulting data extension for the journey entry. To include decisions splits, create additional queries. Consider Marketing Cloud Engagement query performance when designing your solution.

Query activities time out after 30 minutes. Multiple factors can cause query timeouts.
If the query activity is part of an automation, don’t add other activities to the same step of the automation.

Alternatively, you can use an API entry event to add the loyalty member to the journey directly from B2C Commerce or Salesforce Flow. To initiate the journey using REST API event, see Interaction: Fire the Event.
